entry.title: Patience Sorting and Its Generalizations
entry.summary: This dissertation collects together results on Patience Sorting and its generalizations. It incorporates the results of math.CO/0506358, math.CO/0507031, and math.CO/0512122, as well as previously unpublished results.
entry.arxiv:comment: Ph.D. dissertation, 108 pages; uses packages pstricks and youngtab

entry.title: A class of reconstructible graphs
entry.summary: In this paper, we give a class of reconstructible graphs.

entry.title: Reconstruction of p-disconnected graphs
entry.summary: We prove that Kelly-Ulam conjecture is true for p-disconnected graphs.

entry.title: The Stadium Theorem
entry.summary: A proof of a curious planar embedding theorem.

entry.title: The pasch configuration and Steiner triple systems
entry.summary: The pasch configuration and Steiner triple systems

entry.title: On Hall-Littlewood polynomials
entry.summary: An observation on Hall-Littlewood polynomials.

entry.title: Three analogues of Stern's diatomic sequence
entry.summary: We generalize Stern's diatomic sequence in three ways.

entry.title: Hankel Weighing Matrices
entry.summary: We prove a classification theorem for Hankel weighing matrices.

entry.title: On maximal symplectic partial spreads
entry.summary: New types of maximal symplectic partial spreads are constructed.

entry.title: Binomial Andrews-Gordon-Bressoud identities
entry.summary: Binomial versions of the Andrews-Gordon-Bressoud identities are given.

entry.title: On the Union-Closed Sets Conjecture
entry.summary: Several results about the union-closed sets conjecture are presented.

entry.title: Aufgabe VII.47 of Polya-Szego Implies Robbins's Multi-Integral Evaluation
entry.summary: It is remarked that Dave Robbins's Expression for the integral of an alternant over the unit simplex (math.CO/9805108) follows immediately from an excercise in Polya-Szego.

entry.title: Blocking sets in small finite linear spaces II
entry.summary: The contents of this paper has been incorporated into math.CO/0308288.
entry.arxiv:comment: The contents of this paper has been incorporated into math.CO/0308288

entry.title: The Eigenvectors of the Right-Justified Pascal Triangle: A Shorter Proof with Generating Functions
entry.summary: Instead of dealing with cumbersome binomial identities, we prove Callan's result using generating functions.
entry.arxiv:comment: This is related to the recent math.CO/0011081

entry.title: Obtaining hamilton cicuits in graphs and digraphs
entry.summary: This paper improves algorithms given in math.CO/0012036. Although the graph (digraph) becomes non-random as the algorithm proceeds, the probability for success stays the same. We also give examples.

entry.title: Une identité remarquable en théorie des partitions
entry.summary: We prove an identity about partitions, previously conjectured in the study of shifted Jack polynomials (math.CO/9903020). The proof given is using $\lambda$-ring techniques. It would be interesting to obtain a bijective proof.

entry.title: Développements limités et réversion des séries
entry.summary: We prove a few new properties of a Hankel transform related to limited series expansions. This preprint superseed the preprint math.CO/0303221 of the first author.

entry.title: Twenty Open Problems in Enumeration of Matchings
entry.summary: This document is an exposition of an assortment of open problems arising from the exact enumeration of (perfect) matchings of finite graphs. Roughly half have been solved at the time of this writing; see the document "Twenty Open Problems in Enumeration of Matchings: Progress Report" (also available from this server as math.CO/9801061). NOTE: This article has now been superseded by math.CO/9904150.

entry.title: Twenty Open Problems in Enumeration of Matchings: Progress Report
entry.summary: This document is a brief summary of progress that has been made on the problems posed in the document "Twenty Open Problems in Enumeration of Matchings" (also available from this server as math.CO/9801060). NOTE: This article has now been superseded by math.CO/9904150.

entry.title: Proof of a Conjecture of Chan, Robbins, and Yuen
entry.summary: Using the celebrated Morris Constant Term Identity, we deduce a recent conjecture of Chan, Robbins, and Yuen (math.CO/9810154), that asserts that the volume of a certain $n(n-1)/2$-dimensional polytope is given by the product of the first n-1 Catalan numbers.
entry.arxiv:comment: 1 page (plain TeX), proves a conjecture raised in math.CO/9810154. This version also sketches the proofs of conjs. 2 and 3

entry.title: Resonance varieties over fields of positive characteristic
entry.summary: This is a revision and update of the part of the preprint math.CO/0405210 concerning field coefficients, line complexes, and the Hessian arrangement. The material from that paper concerning coefficients in arbitrary commutative rings and the deleted B_3 arrangement will appear separately.
entry.arxiv:comment: Revised version of part of math.CO/0405210

entry.title: Theorems for a Price: Tomorrow's Semi-Rigorous Mathematical Culture
entry.summary: The future of mathematics is described, by using the WZ algorithmic proof theory as a parable.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Notices of the Amer. Math. Soc. 40(1993), 978-981

entry.title: Combinatorial Proofs of Capelli's and Turnbull's Identities from Classical Invariant Theory
entry.summary: Capelli's and Turnbull's classical identities are given elegant combinatorial proofs.

entry.title: How Joe Gillis Discovered Combinatorial Special Function Theory
entry.summary: How Enumerative Combinatorics met Special Functions, thanks to Joe Gillis

entry.title: A note on tiling with integer-sided rectangles
entry.summary: We show how to determine if a given simple rectilinear polygon can be tiled with rectangles, each having an integer side.

entry.title: Partitioned tensor products and their spectra
entry.summary: A pleasant family of graphs defined by Godsil and McKay is shown to have easily computed eigenvalues in many cases.

entry.title: A convolution formula for the Tutte polynomial
entry.summary: We give a convolution formula for the Tutte polynomial T_M (x,y) of a matroid M.

entry.title: Automated counting of LEGO towers
entry.summary: H. N. V. Temperley's method for counting vertically convex polyominoes is modified, generalized, and most importantly, programmed (in Maple).

entry.title: Regressive Ramsey numbers are Ackermannian
entry.summary: We give an elementary proof of the fact that regressive Ramsey numbers are Ackermannian. This fact was first proved by Kanamori and McAloon with mathematical logic techniques.

entry.title: The Abstract Lace Expansion
entry.summary: David Brydges and Thomas Spencer's Lace Expansion is abstracted, and it is shown how it sometimes gives rise to sieves.

entry.title: Dodgson's Determinant-Evaluation Rule proved by Two-Timing Men and Women
entry.summary: The Rev. Dodgson's determinant condensation rule is given a bijective proof.

entry.title: New Lower Bounds for Some Multicolored Ramsey Numbers
entry.summary: We use finite fields and extend a result of Fan Chung to give eight new, nontrivial, lower bounds.

entry.title: An Infinite Antichain of Permutations
entry.summary: We constructively prove that the partially ordered set of finite permutations ordered by deletion of entries contains an infinite antichain.

entry.title: A conjecture about partitions
entry.summary: We present a conjecture about partitions, with a very elementary formulation.

entry.title: Proof of a partition identity conjectured by Lassalle
entry.summary: We prove a partition identity conjectured by Lassalle (Adv. in Appl. Math. 21 (1998), 457-472).

entry.title: Finite posets and Ferrers shapes
entry.summary: A survey on the Greene-Kleitman correspondence, with complete proofs, many of which are new.

entry.title: A continued fraction expansion for a q-tangent function
entry.summary: We prove a continued fraction expansion for a certain q--tangent function that was conjectured by Prodinger.

entry.title: Max-Min Representation of Piecewise Linear Functions
entry.summary: It is shown that a piecewise linear function can be represented as a Max-Min polynomial of its linear components.

entry.title: Kirkman's hypothesis revisited
entry.summary: Watson proved Kirkman's hypothesis (partially solved by Cayley). Using Lagrange Inversion, we drastically shorten Watson's computations and generalize his results at the same time.

entry.title: Some new identities for Schur functions
entry.summary: Some new identities for Schur functions are proved. In particular, we settle in the affirmative a recent conjecture of Ishikawa-Wakayama and solve a problem raised by Bressoud.

entry.title: Short proof of the Gallai-Edmonds Structure Theorem
entry.summary: We derive the Gallai-Edmonds Structure Theorem from Hall's Theorem.

entry.title: The cycle enumerator of unimodal permutations
entry.summary: We give a generating function for the number of unimodal permutations with a given cycle structure.

entry.title: There is no universal countable random-free graph
entry.summary: We consider embeddings between infinite graphs. In particular, We establish that there is no universal element in the class of countable graphs into which the random graph is not embeddable.

entry.title: New Lower Bound Formulas for Multicolored Ramsey Numbers
entry.summary: We give two lower bound formulas for multicolored Ramsey numbers. These formulas improve the bounds for several small multicolored Ramsey numbers.

entry.title: Restricted permutations related to Fibonacci numbers and k-generalized Fibonacci numbers
entry.summary: We give enumerations of various families of restricted permutations involving the Fibonacci numbers or k-generalized Fibonacci numbers.

entry.title: New Identities of Hall-Littlewood Polynomials and Rogers-Ramanujan Type
entry.summary: We prove two new summation formulae of Hall-Littlewood polynomials over partitions into bounded parts and derive some new multiple $q$-identities of Rogers-Ramanujan type.

entry.title: Words restricted by 3-letter generalized multipermutation patterns
entry.summary: We find exact formulas and/or generating functions for the number of words avoiding 3-letter generalized multipermutation patterns and find which of them are equally avoided.

entry.title: Schensted-type correspondence, plactic monoid and jeu de taquin for type C
entry.summary: We use Kashiwara's theory of crystal bases to study the plactic monoid for type C. Then we describe the correponding sliding and bumping algorithms.

entry.title: On the Eulerian Polynomials of Type D
entry.summary: We introduce sub-Eulerian polynomials to count elements of $D_n$ by which a recurrence relation for the Eulerian polynomials of type $D$ is obtained.

entry.title: Discrete subsets of R^2 and the associated distance sets
entry.summary: We prove that a well-distributed subset of R^2 can have a separated distance set only if the distance is induced by a polygon.

entry.title: Pattern containment and combinatorial inequalities
entry.summary: We use a probabilistic method to produce some combinatorial inequalities by considering pattern containment in permutations and words.

entry.title: An Orchard Theorem
entry.summary: We describe a natural way to plant cherry- and plumtrees at prescribed generic locations in an orchard.

entry.title: A conjecture in the problem of rational definite summation
entry.summary: A conjecture is given that, if true, could lead to an algorithm for computing definite sums of rational functions.

entry.title: q-Identities from Lagrange and Newton Interpolation
entry.summary: Combining Newton and Lagrange interpolation, we give $q$-identities which generalize results of Van Hamme, Uchimura, Dilcher and Prodinger.

entry.title: Generalizations of some identities involving the fibonacci numbers
entry.summary: In this paper we study the sum $$\sum_{j_1+j_2+...+j_d=n}\prod_{i=1}^d F_{k\cdot j_i},$$ where $d\geq2$ and $k\geq1$.

entry.title: Polyhedra with specified links
entry.summary: We construct compact polyhedra with $m$-gonal faces whose links are generalized 3-gons. It gives examples of cocompact hyperbolic bildings of type $P(m,3)$. For $m=3$ we get compact spaces covered by Euclidean buildings of type $A_2$.

entry.title: Squaring the terms of an $\ell^{th}$ order linear recurrence
entry.summary: We find an explicit formula for the generating function for the squaring the terms of an $\ell^{th}$ order linear recurrence.

entry.title: Développements limités et la transformée inverse
entry.summary: The generating series associated to a certain sequence of limited Taylor expansions coincides with the continuously iterated Invert Transform and displays thus a nice functional equality.

entry.title: Combinatorial problems in finite geometry and lacunary polynomials
entry.summary: We describe some combinatorial problems in finite projective planes and indicate how R\'edei's theory of lacunary polynomials can be applied to them.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Proceedings of the ICM, Beijing 2002, vol. 3, 537--546

entry.title: A note on avoidable words in squarefree ternary words
entry.summary: We completely characterize the words that can be avoided in infinite squarefree ternary words.

entry.title: On the least exponential growth admitting uncountably many closed permutation classes
entry.summary: We show that the least exponential growth of counting functions which admits uncountably many closed permutation classes lies between 2^n and (2.33529...)^n.

entry.title: The Orchard Morphism
entry.summary: We describe and prove uniqueness of a natural homomorphism between some groups associated to finite sets.

entry.title: An introduction to the dimer model
entry.summary: Lecture notes from a minicourse given at the ICTP in May 2002.

entry.title: On combinatorial compexity of convex sequences
entry.summary: We obtain a good upper bound on the number of solutions of a diophantine equation arising from a strictly convex sequences of real numbers.

entry.title: An Algebraic Approach to Rectangle Packing Problems
entry.summary: A method for converting the geometrical problem of rectangle packing to an algebraic problem of solving a system of polynomial equations is described.

entry.title: There are exponentially many ternary words that avoid abelian cubes
entry.summary: This paper has been withdrawn by the author due to an error in the proof of Theorem 2.

entry.title: Suppressing nonrevisiting paths
entry.summary: Nous refutons, sous une certaine hypothese combinatoire, la "nonrevisiting path conjecture". Abstract: In this article, we give, under some hypothesis, a couterexample to the nonrevisiting path conjecture.

entry.title: $q$-Identities related to overpartitions and divisor functions
entry.summary: We generalize and prove conjectures of Corteel and Lovejoy, related to overpartitions and divisor functions.

entry.title: An (almost) optimal answer to a question by Wilf
entry.summary: We present a class of permutations for which the number of distinctly ordered subsequences of each permutation approaches an almost optimal value as the length of the permutation grows to infinity.

entry.title: q-identities of Fu and Lascoux proved by the q-Rice formula
entry.summary: Two recent $q$--identities of Fu and Lascoux are proved by the $q$--Rice formula.

entry.title: On some $q$-identities related to divisor functions
entry.summary: We give generalizations and simple proofs of some $q$-identities of Dilcher, Fu and Lascoux related to divisor functions.
entry.arxiv:comment: To appear in Adv. in Appl. Math

entry.title: Paperfolding and Catalan numbers
entry.summary: We reprove a few results concerning paperfolding sequences using properties of Catalan numbers modulo 2.

entry.title: A note on equitable colorings of forests
entry.summary: This note gives a short proof on characterizations of a forest to be equitably k-colorable.

entry.title: On the asymptotic value of the choice number of complete multi-partite graphs
entry.summary: We calculate the asymptotic value of the choice number of complete multi-partite graphs.

entry.title: Proof of a conjecture of Hadwiger
entry.summary: Error in proof of theorem 10.
entry.arxiv:comment: Paper withdrawn by author due to an error in proof of theorem 10

entry.title: Statistics on Wreath Products
entry.summary: We present methods of calculating statistics generating functions over the colored permutation groups, and generalizing known theorems from the symmetric groups to general colored permutations groups.

entry.title: The smallest eigenvalue of K_p-free graphs
entry.summary: We give an upper bound on the smallest eigenvalue of the adjacency matrix of graphs with no p-cliques.

entry.title: The Floyd-WarshallAlgorithm and the Asymmetric TSP
entry.summary: We improve proofs in "The Floyd-Warshall Algorithm, the AP and the TSP (III). We also simplify the method for obtaining a good upper bound for an optimal solution.

entry.title: A mathematical proof of four color theorem
entry.summary: This paper has been withdrawn by the author due to a crucial error in last part of proof.

entry.title: Pattern avoiding permutations are context-sensitive
entry.summary: We establish a bijection from the set of all permutations (of a given length) that avoid a pattern $q$ and a context-sensitive language.

entry.title: Symmetric Bush-type Hadamard matrices of order $4m^4$ exist for all odd $m$
entry.summary: Using reversible Hadamard difference sets, we construct symmetric Bush-type Hadamard matrices of order $4m^4$ for all odd integer $m$.

entry.title: Two multicolor Ramsey numbers
entry.summary: Two new bounds for multicolor Ramsey numbers are proved: $R(K_3,K_3,C_4,C_4)\geq 27$ and $R_4(C_4)\leq 19$.

entry.title: Intersection properties of relations
entry.summary: We derive some equalities for relations on the algebra A, under the assumption that every subalgebra of A $\times$ A is congruence modular.

entry.title: On limits of finite graphs
entry.summary: We prove that for any weakly convergent sequence of finite graphs with bounded vertex degrees, there exists a topological limit graphing.

entry.title: A new class of reconstructible graphs
entry.summary: In this paper, we give a new class of reconstructible graphs, which is an extension of my paper `A class of reconstructible graphs'.

entry.title: Parameters Changes for Generalized Power Series
entry.summary: Introduction revised, representations of generalized power series reformulated, references updated.

entry.title: q-Catalan numbers and q-Narayana polynomials
entry.summary: In this note we show that various natural q-analogues of the Catalan numbers can be obtained in a uniform way. Furthermore we compute their Hankel determinants.

entry.title: Distances between the winning numbers in Lottery
entry.summary: We prove an interesting fact about Lottery: the winning 6 numbers (out of 49) in the game of the Lottery contain two consecutive numbers with a surprisingly high probability (almost 50%).

entry.title: Binomial posets with non-isomorphic intervals
entry.summary: The confluent binomial posets with the atomic function A(n) = max (1,2^(n-2)) are classified. In particular, it is shown that in general there are non-isomorphic intervals of the same length.

entry.title: Arithmetic properties of q-Fibonacci numbers and q-Pell numbers
entry.summary: We investigate some arithmetic properties of the q-Fibonacci numbers and the q-Pell numbers.

entry.title: Two identities of derangements
entry.summary: In this note, we present two new identities for derangements. As a corollary, we have a combinatorial proof of the irreducibility of the standard representation of symmetric groups.

entry.title: Binary words containing infinitely many overlaps
entry.summary: We characterize the squares occurring in infinite overlap-free binary words and construct various alpha power-free binary words containing infinitely many overlaps.

entry.title: Cobordism of words
entry.summary: We introduce an equivalence relation, called cobordism, for words and study cobordism invariants of words inspired by methods of low-dimensional topology.

entry.title: When is 0.999... equal to 1?
entry.summary: A doubly infinite sum, numerically evaluated at between 0.999 and 1.001, turns out to have a nice value.

entry.title: On the formula of Goulden and Rattan for Kerov polynomials
entry.summary: We give a simple proof of an explicit formula for Kerov polynomials. This formula is closely related to a formula of Goulden and Rattan.

entry.title: New upper bound for a class of vertex Folkman numbers
entry.summary: We improve the previuosly known bound for some vertex Folkman numbers.

entry.title: An example of a 16-vertex Folkman edge (3,4)-graph without 8-cliques
entry.summary: In this paper we prove a new upper bouhd on an edge Folkman number. In a previous paper we have proved that this bound is exact.

entry.title: Cycles and Stability
entry.summary: We derive a number of extremal and Ramsey stability results for cycles.

entry.title: A note on some binomial sums
entry.summary: Modifying an idea of E. Brietzke we give simple proofs for the recurrence relations of some sequences of binomial sums which have previously been obtained by other more complicated methods.

entry.title: On the outerplanar crossing numbers of complete multipartite graphs
entry.summary: We calculate the outerplanar crossing numbers of complete multipartite graphs which have $n$ partite sets with $m$ vertices and one partite set with $p$ vertices, where either $p|mn$ or $mn|p$.

entry.title: Face vectors of flag complexes
entry.summary: A conjecture of Kalai and Eckhoff that the face vector of an arbitrary flag complex is also the face vector of some particular balanced complex is verified.

entry.title: Laplacians on shifted multicomplexes
entry.summary: We define the Laplacian operator on finite multicomplexes and give a formula for its spectra in the case of shifted multicomplexes.

entry.title: Eigenvectors and Reconstruction
entry.summary: In this paper, I study the simple eigenvectors of two hypomorphic matrices using linear algebra. I give new proofs of results of Godsil and MaKay.

entry.title: On Sjostrand's skew sign-imbalance identity
entry.summary: We give a short proof of Sjostrand's sign-imbalance identity for skew shapes using the domino Cauchy identity.

entry.title: The Slope Polynomial and Collinear Points in Permutations
entry.summary: Withdrawn due to fatal errors.

entry.title: Riemann sums over polytopes
entry.summary: We show that the Euler-MacLaurin formula for Riemann sums has an n-dimensional analogue in which intervals on the line get replaced by convex polytopes.

entry.title: Cliques and the Spectral Radius
entry.summary: We present a number of relations involving the number of cliques in a graph and its spectral radius.

entry.title: New proof of a Theorem on k-hypertournament losing scores
entry.summary: In this paper, we give a new and short proof of a Theorem on k-hypertournament losing scores due to Zhou et al.[7].

entry.title: A simple bijection between permutation tableaux and permutations
entry.summary: We present a simple a bijection between permutations of $\{1,..., n\}$ with $k$ descents and permutation tableaux of length $n$ with $k$ columns.

entry.title: Finite q-identities related to well-known theorems of Euler and Gauss
entry.summary: We give generalizations of a finite version of Euler's pentagonal number theorem and of a q-identity of Gauss.

entry.title: Cordial Deficiency
entry.summary: We introduce two new measures of the noncordiality of a graph. We then calculate the values of these measures for various families of noncordial graphs. We also determine exactly which of the M\"obius ladders are cordial.

entry.title: Some results and conjectures about recurrence relations for certain sequences of binomial sums
entry.summary: We give some results and conjectures about recurrence relations for certain sequences of binomial sums.

entry.title: Random Discrete Matrices
entry.summary: In this survey, we discuss some basic problems concerning random matrices with discrete distributions. Several new results, tools and conjectures will be presented.

entry.title: Integrity of ghosts
entry.summary: Sequences of traces of powers of integral matrices are characterized.The result can be used can be used in character tables of e.g. the symmetric group.

entry.title: A Realization of Graph-Associahedra
entry.summary: Given any finite graph, we offer a simple realization of the graph-associahedron polytope using integer coordinates.

entry.title: The Moore bound for Spectral Radius
entry.summary: We give an upper bound on the largest eigenvalue of a graph of given order, size, and girth.
entry.arxiv:comment: The second version corrects a stupid mistake

entry.title: On Goulden-Jackson's determinantal expression for the immanant
entry.summary: In 1992, Goulden and Jackson found a beautiful determinantal expression for the immanant of a matrix. This paper proves the same result combinatorially.

entry.title: Hadamard matrices of order 764 exist
entry.summary: We construct two Hadamard matrices of order 764. Both are of Goethals-Seidel type.

entry.title: On the automorphism group of a possible symmetric $(81,16,3)$ design
entry.summary: In this paper we study the automorphism group of a possible symmetric $(81,16,3)$ design.

entry.title: On the decycling of powers and products of cycles
entry.summary: We calculate exact values of the decycling numbers of $C_{m} \times C_{n}$ for $m=3,4$, of $C_{n}^{2}$, and of $C_{n}^{3}$.

entry.title: Gallai Multigraphs
entry.summary: A complete edge-colored graph or multigraph is called Gallai if it lacks rainbow triangles. We give a construction of all finite Gallai multigraphs.

entry.title: A solid angle polynomial with negative coefficients
entry.summary: This article has been replaced by arXiv:0906.4031

entry.title: Stability for large forbidden subgraphs
entry.summary: We extend the classical stability theorem of Erdos and Simonovits for forbidden graphs of logarithmic order.

entry.title: Rogers-Szego polynomials and Hall-Littlewood symmetric functions
entry.summary: We use Rogers-Szego polynomials to unify some well-known identities for Hall-Littlewood symmetric functions due to Macdonald and Kawanaka.

entry.title: Human proofs of identities by Osburn and Schneider
entry.summary: Osburn and Schneider derived several combinatorial identities involving harmonic numbers using the computer programm Sigma. Here, they are derived by partial fraction decomposition and creative telescoping.

entry.title: Fair Triangulations
entry.summary: We describe the statistics of checkerboard triangulations obtained by colouring black every other triangle in triangulations of convex polygons.

entry.title: Homomorphisms and Structural Properties of Relational Systems
entry.summary: Two main topics are considered: The characterisation of finite homomorphism dualities for relational structures, and the splitting property of maximal antichains in the homomorphism order.

entry.title: Graphs with many copies of a given subgraph
entry.summary: We show that if a graph G of order n contains many copies of a given subgraph H, then it contains a blow-up of H of order log n.

entry.title: Szemeredi-Trotter type theorem and sum-product estimate in finite fields
entry.summary: We study a Szemer\'edi-Trotter type theorem in finite fields. We then use this theorem to obtain an improved sum-product estimate in finite fields.

entry.title: Condensation of Determinants
entry.summary: In this paper we tried to condense the determinant of n square matrix to the determinant of (n - 1) square matrix with the mathematical proof.

entry.title: The copies of any permutation pattern are asymptotically normal
entry.summary: We prove that the number of copies of any given permutation pattern $q$ has an asymptotically normal distribution in random permutations.

entry.title: 9 Divides no Odd Fibonacci
entry.summary: I discuss numbers that divide no odd Fibonacci. Number 9 plays a special role among such numbers.

entry.title: One way cuts in oriented graphs
entry.summary: This paper has been withdrawn by the author.
entry.arxiv:comment: This paper has been withdrawn by the author. now included in "Subgraphs of weakly quasi-random oriented graphs"

entry.title: A theorem on the cores of partitions
entry.summary: If s and t are relatively prime positive integers we show that the s-core of a t-core partition is again a t-core partition

entry.title: Improvement of graph theory Wei`s inequality
entry.summary: In this paper we give a generalization of a result of Wei.

entry.title: q-Abel polynomials
entry.summary: This note gives a simple approach to q-analogues of some results associated with Abel polynomials.

entry.title: Reduced Incidence algebras description of cobweb posets and KoDAGs
entry.summary: After identifying the reduced incidence algebra of an arbitrary cobweb poset the very first properties of these algebras are being disclosed.

entry.title: Acyclic edge coloring
entry.summary: This paper has been withdrawn by the author due to an error in the proof.

entry.title: Number Gossip
entry.summary: This article covers my talk at the Gathering for Gardner 2008, with some additions.

entry.title: New hook length formulas for binary trees
entry.summary: We find two new hook length formulas for binary trees. The particularity of our formulas is that the hook length $h_v$ appears as an exponent.

entry.title: Some conjectures about q-Fibonacci polynomials
entry.summary: In this paper we state some conjectures about q-Fibonacci polynomials which for q=1 reduce to well-known results about Fibonacci numbers and Fibonacci polynomials.

entry.title: An elementary proof of a series evaluation in terms of harmonic numbers
entry.summary: An elementary proof of an identity by Lyons, Paule and Riese is given. It is simpler than all the 3 published proofs.

entry.title: Restricted centrosymmetric permutations
entry.summary: The paper was withdrawn because of its significant overlap with a paper appeared recently.

entry.title: Recurrence relations for powers of q-Fibonacci polynomials
entry.summary: We derive some q-analogs of Euler-Cassini-type identities and of recurrence formulas for powers of Fibonacci polynomials.

entry.title: New Upper Bound for the Edge Folkman Number Fe(3,5;13)
entry.summary: In this paper we prove that the edge Folkman number Fe(3,5;13) is not greater than 21.

entry.title: Making research on symmetric functions using MuPAD-Combinat
entry.summary: We present an overview of the implementation of symmetric functions in MuPAD-Combinat. We also explain how to interface C++ programs with MuPAD in order to make efficient research during concrete work sessions.

entry.title: Orthogonal systems in vector spaces over finite fields
entry.summary: We prove that if a subset of the d-dimensional vector space over a finite field is large enough, then it contains many k-tuples of mutually orthogonal vectors.

entry.title: A characterization of substitutive sequences using return words
entry.summary: We prove that a sequence is primitive substitutive if and only if the set of its derived sequences is finite; we defined these sequences here.

entry.title: Quantized dual graded graphs
entry.summary: We study quantized dual graded graphs, which are graphs equipped with linear operators satisfying the relation DU - qUD = rI. We construct examples based upon: the Fibonacci poset, permutations, standard Young tableau, and plane binary trees.

entry.title: Proof of Han's Hook Expansion Conjecture
entry.summary: We prove a conjecture by Guo-Niu Han which interpolates between two known hook expansion formulas.

entry.title: Squishing dimers on the hexagon lattice
entry.summary: We describe an operation on dimer configurations on the hexagon lattice, called "squishing", and use this operation to explain some of the properties of dimer generating functions.

entry.title: The Bi-Musquash Conjecture
entry.summary: D.R. Woodall's definition of a 'musquash' is extended to that of a 'bi-musquash' and the existence/uniqueness of these is discussed.

entry.title: Tableaux Combinatorics for the Asymmetric Exclusion Process II
entry.summary: The results of this paper have been subsumed by those of our new paper arXiv:0910.1858

entry.title: The mutation class of $D_n$ quivers
entry.summary: We give an explicit description of the mutation class of quivers of type D.

entry.title: On a generalization of P(3,n)
entry.summary: By using techniques of poset representation theory, we present a formula for the number of partitions of a positive integer into three polygonal numbers.

entry.title: On the nonexistence of ternary extremal self-dual codes
entry.summary: In this note, we give a new nonexistence result of ternary extremal self-dual codes.

entry.title: Hankel determinants of q-exponential polynomials
entry.summary: We give simple proofs for the Hankel determinants of q-exponential polynomials.

entry.title: Finite Implication Algebras
entry.summary: We consider several distinct characterizations of finite implication algebras. One of these leads to a new characterization of Boolean polymatroids.

entry.title: Regev's theorem via rectangles
entry.summary: This paper has been withdrawn by the author due to a crucial error in equation (51).

entry.title: Free cubic implication algebras
entry.summary: We construct free cubic implication algebras with finitely many generators, and determine the size of these algebras.

entry.title: A simple approach to some Hankel determinants
entry.summary: I give simple elementary proofs for some well-known Hankel determinants and their q-analogues.

entry.title: On Reichenbach's causal betweenness
entry.summary: We characterize, by easily verifiable properties, abstract ternary relations isomorphic to the causal betweenness introduced by Hans Reichenbach.

entry.title: One-parameter Generalizations of Ramanujan's Formula for $π$
entry.summary: Several terminating generalizations of Ramanujan's formula for $\frac{1}{\pi}$ with complete WZ proofs are given.

entry.title: Note on half-cube embeddings
entry.summary: Results are well-known

entry.title: On the diagonal hooks of a symmetric partition
entry.summary: Using only a symmetric p-core partition and p-quotient, we give an explicit formula for the set of diagonal hook lengths of the associated symmetric partition.

entry.title: On The Vertex Folkman Numbers $F_v(\underbrace{2,...,2}_r;r-1)$ and $F_v(\underbrace{2,...,2}_r;r-2)$%
entry.summary: In this paper several Folkman numbers are computed.

entry.title: A short proof of Combinatorial Nullstellensatz
entry.summary: In this note we give a short, direct proof of the well known Combinatorial Nullstellensatz.

entry.title: The Link Component Number of Suspended Trees
entry.summary: This paper provides a relationship between a geometric structure of a suspended tree and the number of link components of the associated link diagram.

entry.title: Higher dimensional Moore bounds
entry.summary: We prove upper bounds on the face numbers of simplicial complexes in terms on their girths, in analogy with the Moore bound from graph theory. Our definition of girth generalizes the usual definition for graphs.

entry.title: A combinatorial survey of identities for the double factorial
On the circumference, connectivity and dominating cycles
entry.summary: Every 4-connected graph with minimum degree $\delta$ and connectivity $\kappa$ either has a cycle of length at least $4\delta-2\kappa$ or has a dominating cycle.

entry.title: Domination number of cubic graphs with large girth
entry.summary: We show that every n-vertex cubic graph with girth at least g have domination number at most 0.299871n+O(n/g)<3n/10+O(n/g).

entry.title: Latin trades and simplicial complexes
entry.summary: In this note we introduce the concept of the trade space of a latin square. Computations using Sage and the GAP package Simplicial Homology are presented.

entry.title: Betti numbers are testable
entry.summary: We prove that the Betti numbers of simplicial complexes of bounded vertex degrees are testable in constant time.
entry.arxiv:comment: to appear in the volume "Fete of Combinatorics and Computer Science"

entry.title: Generating Functions of Nestohedra and Applications
entry.summary: We examine the family of nestohedra resulting from the complete bipartite graph through the medium of a generating function and demonstrate some of their combinatorial invariants.

entry.title: On Coloring the Odd-Distance Graph
entry.summary: We present a proof, using spectral techniques, that there is no finite measurable coloring of the odd-distance graph.

entry.title: Determinants of adjacency matrices of graphs
entry.summary: We study the set of all determinants of adjacency matrices of graphs with a given number of vertices.

entry.title: Hankel determinants of generalized q-exponential polynomials
entry.summary: Recently I. Mezo studied a simple but interesting generalization of the exponential polynomials. In this note I consider two q-analogues of these polynomials and compute their Hankel determinants.

entry.title: Extremal Betti numbers of Rips complexes
entry.summary: Upper bounds on the topological Betti numbers of Vietoris-Rips complexes are established, and examples of such complexes with high Betti numbers are given.

entry.title: A Probability Method to Prove Combinatorial Identities
entry.summary: A probability method is provided to prove three classes of combinatorial identities. The method is extremely simple, only one step after the proper probability setup.

entry.title: Some Identities Involving Three Kinds of Counting Numbers
entry.summary: In this note, we present several identities involving binomial coefficients and the two kind of Stirling numbers.

entry.title: Recurrent words with constant Abelian complexity
entry.summary: We prove the non-existence of recurrent words with constant Abelian complexity containing 4 or more distinct letters. This answers a question of Richomme et al.

entry.title: On Visibility and Blockers
entry.summary: This expository paper discusses some conjectures related to visibility and blockers for sets of points in the plane.

entry.title: An Inductive Proof of Whitney's Broken Circuit Theorem
entry.summary: We present a new proof of Whitney's broken circuit theorem based on induction on the number of edges and the deletion-contraction formula.

entry.title: The critical group of $C_4\times C_n$
entry.summary: In this paper, the critical group structure of the Cartesian product graph $C_4\times C_n$ is determined, where $n\ge 3$.

entry.title: Bounds on some edge Folkman numbers
entry.summary: We give some bounds on edge Folkman numbers.

entry.title: A note on hook length formulas for trees
entry.summary: In this short note we discuss recent results on hook length formulas of trees unifying some earlier results, and explain hook length formulas naturally associated to families of increasingly labelled trees.

entry.title: Note on Doron Zeilberger's paper: ${5 \choose 2}$ proofs that ${n \choose k} \leq {n \choose {k+1}}$ if $k < n/2$
entry.summary: We present yet another algebraic proof of the unimodality of the binomial coefficients.

entry.title: Twisting the Stern sequence
entry.summary: We describe a twisted version of the Stern sequence and study a few of its properties.

entry.title: Circular Sequences and the Diameter of Multipermutohedra
entry.summary: We derive bounds on the number of switches at an arbitrary set of positions in a circular sequence of permutations and relate them to the diameter of Multipermutohedra.

entry.title: Flag f-vectors of colored complexes
entry.summary: It is shown that conditions stronger in a certain sense than color-shifting cannot be placed on the class of colored complexes without changing the characterization of the flag f-vectors.

entry.title: A characterization of Q-polynomial association schemes
entry.summary: We prove a necessary and sufficient condition for a symmetric association scheme to be a Q-polynomial scheme.

entry.title: A Counting Proof of the Graham Pollak Theorem
entry.summary: We give a counting based proof of the Graham Pollak Theorem

entry.title: An Improved Upper Bound for the Sum-free Subset Constant
entry.summary: We show that the optimal constant in Erd\"{o}s' sum-free subset theorem cannot be larger than $11/28 \approx .393$.

entry.title: Cyclic sieving phenomenon in non-crossing connected graphs
entry.summary: We prove an instance of the cyclic sieving phenomenon in non-crossing connected graphs, as conjectured by S.-P. Eu.

entry.title: The number of ribbon Schur functions
entry.summary: We present a formula for the number of distinct ribbon Schur functions of given size and height.

entry.title: Probabilistic Representation of Bernoulli, Euler and Carlitz Hermite Polynomials
entry.summary: We revisit in a probabilistic framework the umbral approach of Bernoulli, Euler and Carlitz Hermite polynomials by Gessel [1].

entry.title: Considering Adelman's Shortest Permutation Strings
entry.summary: In this report, we consider Adelman's algorithm for generating shortest permutation strings. We introduce a new representation approach which reveals some properties of Adelman's algorithm.

entry.title: Covering numbers for graphs and hypergraphs
entry.summary: This paper has been withdrawn, as it has been merged into arXiv:1009.6144

entry.title: On the chromatic numbers of spheres in $ {\mathbb R}^n $
entry.summary: In this paper, we obtain new asymptotic lower bounds for the chromatic numbers of spheres.

entry.title: Approximations to the Kruskal-Katona theorem
entry.summary: Approximations to the Kruskal-Katona theorem are stated and proven. These approximations are weaker than the theorem, but much easier to work with numerically.

entry.title: Generalized Hamming schemes
entry.summary: We introduce a class of association schemes that generalizes the Hamming scheme. We derive generating functions for their eigenvalues, and use these to obtain a version of MacWilliams theorem.

entry.title: A note on V-binomials recurrence for Lucas companion to $U_n$ sequence $V_n$
entry.summary: The looked for V-binomials recurrence for Lucas companion to $U_n$ sequence $V_n$ is delivered

entry.title: Properties of the poset of Dyck paths ordered by inclusion
entry.summary: An expository summary of properties of the poset of Dyck paths ordered by inclusion.
entry.arxiv:comment: 60 pages; for reading course on combinatorics

entry.title: Idempotents with polynomial coefficients
entry.summary: We combine Young idempotents in the group algebra of the symmetric group with the action of the symmetric group on products of Vandermonde determinants to obtain idempotents with polynomial coefficients.

entry.title: A combinatorial proof of Guo's multi-generalization of Munarini's identity
entry.summary: We give a combinatorial proof of Guo's multi-generalization of Munarini's identity, answering a question of Guo.

entry.title: A remark on some bases in the Hecke algebra
entry.summary: We consider some bases in the Hecke algebra and exhibit certain dualities between them.
entry.arxiv:comment: 6 pages, exposition streamlined, all comments welcome

entry.title: On Skew Hadamard difference sets
entry.summary: In this paper we construct exponentionally many non-isomorphic skew Hadamard difference sets over an elementary abelian group of order $q^3$.

entry.title: Some inversion formulas and formulas for Stirling numbers
entry.summary: In the paper we present some new inversion formulas and two new formulas for Stirling numbers.

entry.title: Avoiding 3/2-powers over the natural numbers
entry.summary: In this paper we answer the following question: what is the lexicographically least sequence over the natural numbers that avoids 3/2-powers?

entry.title: An improved sum-product estimate for general finite fields
entry.summary: This paper improves on a sum-product estimate obtained by Katz and Shen for subsets of a finite field whose order is not prime.

entry.title: Extremal Infinite Graph Theory
entry.summary: We survey various aspects of infinite extremal graph theory and prove several new results. The lead role play the parameters connectivity and degree. This includes the end degree. Many open problems are suggested.

entry.title: Pattern Matching in the Cycle Structure of Permutations
entry.summary: In this paper, we study the occurrence of patterns in the cycle structures of permutations.

entry.title: Note on antichain cutsets in discrete semimodular lattices
entry.summary: The characterization of level sets of finite Boolean lattices as antichain cutsets, due to Rival and Zaguia, is seen to hold in all discrete semimodular lattices.

entry.title: Open problems in Costas arrays
entry.summary: A collection of open problems in Costas arrays is presented, classified into several categories, along with the context in which they arise.

entry.title: Some Combinatorial Identities from the Random Walk
entry.summary: Eight combinatorial identities are listed and proved by counting paths in the one-dimensional random walk. Four of these identities are assumed to be new.

entry.title: A Variant $β$-Wythoff Nim on Beatty's Theorem
entry.summary: We give short rules for two-pile take-away games satisfying that a pair of complementary homogeneous Beatty sequences together with $(0,0)$ constitute a complete set of $P$-positions.

entry.title: On wreath products of cyclic schemes
entry.summary: We describe explicitly the algebraic structure of the Terwilliger algebra of wreath products of cyclic schemes.

entry.title: On the super connectivity of Kronecker products of graphs
entry.summary: In this paper we present the super connectivity of Kronecker product of a general graph and a complete graph.

entry.title: The eigenvalues of $q$-Kneser graphs
entry.summary: In this note, we prove some combinatorial identities and obtain a simple form of the eigenvalues of $q$-Kneser graphs.

entry.title: 5-choosability of graphs with 2 crossings
entry.summary: We show that every graph with two crossings is 5-choosable. We also prove that every graph which can be made planar by removing one edge is 5-choosable.

entry.title: t-singular linear spaces
entry.summary: As a generalization of singular linear spaces, we introduce the concept of t-singular linear spaces, make some anzahl formulas of subspaces, and determine the suborbits of t-singular linear groups.

entry.title: A solution of an equivalence problem for semisimple cyclic codes
entry.summary: In this paper we propose an efficient solution of an equivalence problem for semisimple cyclic codes.

entry.title: Erratum to: Lattice point methods for combinatorial games
entry.summary: We correct Definition 6.3, Proposition 6.7, and Section 7 in the published version of our paper.

entry.title: A graph-theoretical axiomatization of oriented matroids
entry.summary: We characterize which systems of sign vectors are the cocircuits of an oriented matroid in terms of the cocircuit graph.

entry.title: 4-critical wheel graphs of higher order
entry.summary: 4-critical wheel graphs of higher order are considered concerning their belonging to free-planar or free-Hadwiger classes.

entry.title: On AZ-style identity
entry.summary: The AZ identity is a generalization of the LYM-inequality. In this paper, we will give a generalization of the AZ identity.

entry.title: A note on vertex partitions
entry.summary: We prove a general lemma about partitioning the vertex set of a graph into subgraphs of bounded degree. This lemma extends a sequence of results of Lov\'asz, Catlin, Kostochka and Rabern.

entry.title: A Size Bound for Hamilton Cycles
entry.summary: Every graph of size $q$ (the number of edges) and minimum degree $\delta$ is hamiltonian if $q\le\delta^2+\delta-1$. The result is sharp.

entry.title: Scott's induced subdivision conjecture for maximal triangle-free graphs
entry.summary: Scott conjectured that the class of graphs with no induced subdivision of a given graph is $\chi$-bounded. We verify his conjecture for maximal triangle-free graphs.

entry.title: The enumeration of permutations avoiding 2143 and 4231
entry.summary: We enumerate the pattern class Av(2143,4231) and completely describe its permutations. The main tools are simple permutations and monotone grid classes.

entry.title: Colouring stability two unit disk graphs
entry.summary: We prove that every stability two unit disk graph has chromatic number at most 3/2 times its clique number.

entry.title: Un invariant remarquable des polytopes simples
entry.summary: We associate an integer to any simple polytope and we study its properties.

entry.title: Note on parity factors of regular graphs
entry.summary: In this paper, we obtain a sufficient condition for the existence of parity factors in a regular graph in terms of edge-connectivity. Moreover, we also show that our condition is sharp.

entry.title: Excluding Degree Sequences of Cycles
entry.summary: In this paper, we characterize the degree sequences excluding the degree sequence of a square in terms of forcibly chordal graphs, and we prove several related results.

entry.title: A short proof for Dougall's $_2H_2$-series identity
entry.summary: According to Chen and Fu's method, we offer a short proof for Dougall's $_2H_2$-series identity.

entry.title: A probabilistic approach to some binomial identities
entry.summary: Classical binomial identities are established by giving probabilistic interpretations to the summands. The examples include Vandermonde identity and some generalizations.

entry.title: Two-Color Babylon
entry.summary: We solve the game of Babylon when played with chips of two colors, giving a winning strategy for the second player in all previously unsolved cases.

entry.title: On new sum-product type estimates
entry.summary: New lower bounds involving sum, difference, product, and ratio sets for $A\subset \C$ are given.

entry.title: Log-concavity of face vectors of cyclic and ordinary polytopes
entry.summary: Ordinary polytopes are known as a non-simplicial generalization of the cyclic polytopes. The face vectors of ordinary polytopes are shown to be log-concave.

entry.title: Summation formulae for $q$-Watson type $_4φ_3$-series
entry.summary: According to the method of series rearrangement, we establish two families of summation formulae for $q$-Watson type $_4\phi_3$-series.

entry.title: Verification of Binomial theorem and Chu-Vandermonde convolution by the finite difference method
entry.summary: In this note, we show that Binomial theorem and Chu-Vandermonde convolution can both be verified by the finite difference method.

entry.title: A new family of polynomial identities for computing determinants
entry.summary: We give new definitions for the determinant over commutative ring $K$, noncommutative ring $\mathbf{K}$, noncommutative ring $\mathcal{K}$ with associative powers, over noncommutative nonassociative ring $\mathfrak{K}$, and study their properties.

entry.title: A projection construction for semifields
entry.summary: Simple constructions are given for finite semifields that include as special cases both old semifields and recently constructed semifields.

entry.title: Chu-Vandermonde convolution and harmonic number identities
entry.summary: By applying the derivative operators to Chu-Vandermonde convolution, several general harmonic number identities are established.

entry.title: Sets with no solutions to $x+y=3z$
entry.summary: This short note gives an upper bound on the measure of sets $A\subset [0,1]$ such that $x+y=3z$ has no solutions in $A$.

entry.title: Roth type theorems in finite groups
entry.summary: We prove Roth type theorems in finite groups. Our main tool is the Triangle Removal Lemma of Ruzsa and Szemer\'edi.

entry.title: Integral Representation and Computation a Multiple Sum in the Theory of Cubature Formulas
entry.summary: In this article we furnish a new simple proof of a hard identity from the theory of cubature formulas via the method of coefficients.

entry.title: A characterization of skew Hadamard matrices and doubly regular tournaments
entry.summary: We give a new characterization of skew Hadamard matrices of size $n$ in terms of the data of the spectra of tournaments of size $n-2$.

entry.title: Clustering words
entry.summary: We characterize words which cluster under the Burrows-Wheeler transform as those words $w$ such that $ww$ occurs in a trajectory of an interval exchange transformation, and build examples of clustering words.

entry.title: An expansion formula for the inversions and excedances in the symmetric group
entry.summary: We prove a recent conjecture of Blanco and Petersen (arXiv:1206.0803v2) about an expansion formula for inversions and excedances in the symmetric group.

entry.title: A new upper bound for 1324-avoiding permutations
entry.summary: We prove that the number of 1324-avoiding permutations of length n is less than (7+4\sqrt{3})^n.

entry.title: Finding msr of a given graph of at most seven vertices by giving vector representations
entry.summary: In this paper, we study the minimum rank among positive semidefinite matrices with a given graph of at most seven vertices (msr) by giving vector representations.

entry.title: The abelian complexity of the paperfolding word
entry.summary: We show that the abelian complexity function of the ordinary paperfolding word is a 2-regular sequence.

entry.title: A modular Szemeredi-Trotter theorem for hyperbolas
entry.summary: We establish a Szemeredi-Trotter type result for hyperbolas in $\mathbb F_p\times\mathbb F_p$

entry.title: Unimodular equivalence of order and chain polytopes
entry.summary: The problem when the order polytope and the chain polytope of a finite partially ordered set are unimodularly equivalent will be solved.

entry.title: On some monotonic combinatorial sequences conjectures
entry.summary: Here we prove some conjectures on the monotony of combinatorial sequences from the recent preprint of Zhi--Wei Sun.

entry.title: Finite Polytopes have Finite Regular Covers
entry.summary: We prove that any finite, abstract n-polytope is covered by a finite, abstract regular n-polytope.

entry.title: Characterizing partition functions of the spin model by rank growth
entry.summary: We characterize which graph invariants are partition functions of a spin model over the complex numbers, in terms of the rank growth of associated `connection matrices'.

entry.title: A Note on Hamilton Cycles
entry.summary: If $G$ is a more than one tough graph on $n$ vertices with $\delta\ge \frac{n}{2}-a$ for a given $a>0$ and $n$ is large enough then $G$ is hamiltonian.

entry.title: Minimal bricks have many vertices of small degree
entry.summary: We prove that every minimal brick on n vertices has at least n/9 vertices of degree at most 4.

entry.title: Triakis Solids and Harmonic Functions
entry.summary: We describe the harmonic functions for certain isohedral triakis solids. They are the first examples for which polyhedral harmonics is strictly larger than group harmonics.

entry.title: The Lonely Runner Conjecture
entry.summary: A detailed survey of the Lonely Runner Conjecture and its connection between Diophantine approximation and View-obstruction problems.

entry.title: Bent functions generalizing Dillon's partial spread functions
entry.summary: This note presents generalizations of the partial spread bent functions introduced by Dillon, as well as the corresponding relative difference sets in nonabelian groups.

entry.title: Three-class association schemes from cyclotomy
entry.summary: We give three constructions of three-class association schemes as fusion schemes of the cyclotomic scheme, two of which are primitive

entry.title: Circular flow number of highly edge connected signed graphs
entry.summary: This paper proves that for any positive integer $k$, every essentially $(2k+1)$-unbalanced $(12k-1)$-edge connected signed graph has circular flow number at most $2+\frac 1k$.

entry.title: Chromatic polynomials of simplicial complexes
entry.summary: We consider s-chromatic polynomials of simplicial complexes, higher dimensional analogues of chromatic polynomials for graphs.

entry.title: A note on strong edge-colorings of 2-degenerate graphs
entry.summary: We show that every 2-degenerate graph with maximum degree $\Delta$ has a strong edge-coloring with at most $8\Delta-4$ colors.

entry.title: A bipartite graph with non-unimodal independent set sequence
entry.summary: We show that the independent set sequence of a bipartite graph need not be unimodal.

entry.title: Prüfer codes for hypertrees
entry.summary: We describe a new Pr\"ufer code which works also for infinite trees.

entry.title: A Witt type formula
entry.summary: This paper investigates some combinatorial and algebraic properties of a Witt type formula for graphs.

author.name: G. A. T. F. da Costa

entry.title: A quick construction of mutually orthogonal sudoku squares
entry.summary: For any odd prime power q we provide a quick construction of a complete family of q(q-1) mutually orthogonal sudoku squares of order q^2.

entry.title: An upper bound for nonnegative rank
entry.summary: We provide a nontrivial upper bound for the nonnegative rank of rank-three matrices, which allows us to prove that [6(n+1)/7] linear inequalities suffice to describe a convex n-gon up to a linear projection.

entry.title: Finite Decomposition Semigroups
entry.summary: In this paper, we explain the importance of finite decomposition semigroups and present two theorems related to their structure.

entry.title: The Mimimum 3-Covering Energy of Complete Graphs
entry.summary: In this paper we introduce a different kind of graph energy, the minimum 3-covering energy of a graph, and determine the minimum 3-covering energy of complete graphs.

entry.title: DeBruijn Strings, Double Helices, and the Ehrenfeucht-Mycielski Mechanism
entry.summary: We revisit the pseudo-random sequence introduced by Ehrenfeucht and Mycielski and its connections with DeBruijn strings.

entry.title: A Model of the Witt Design $W_{12}$ based on Quadrics of PG(2,3)
entry.summary: An elementary geometric proof for the existence of Witt's 5-(12,6,1) design is given.

entry.title: One conjecture about size of Sidon sets
entry.summary: We prove that maximal cardinality of the Sidon set from $[n]$ exceeds $\sqrt{n}
entry.arxiv:comment: This paper has been withdrawn by the author to make corrections

entry.title: Lambda Determinants
entry.summary: In this paper we prove a homogenous generalization of the lambda determinant formula of Mills, Robbins and Rumsey. In our formula the parameters depends on two indices. Our result also extends a recent formula of Di Francesco.

entry.title: On the complexity of Boolean matrix ranks
entry.summary: We construct a reduction which proves that the fooling set number and the determinantal rank of a Boolean matrix are NP-hard to compute.

entry.title: Permutations avoiding 4321 and 3241 have an algebraic generating function
entry.summary: We show that permutations avoiding both of the (classical) patterns 4321 and 3241 have the algebraic generating function conjectured by Vladimir Kruchinin.

entry.title: Partition regularity of a system of De and Hindman
entry.summary: We prove that a certain matrix, which is not image partition regular over R near zero, is image partition regular over N. This answers a question of De and Hindman.

entry.title: On monotonicity-preserving perturbations of $M$-matrices
entry.summary: We obtain an explicit analytical sufficient condition on $E$ that ensures the monotonicity of the matrix $M+E$, where $M$ is an $M$-matrix.

entry.title: Nonnegative rank of a matrix with one negative eigenvalue
entry.summary: We show that a rank-three symmetric matrix with exactly one negative eigenvalue can have arbitrarily large nonnegative rank.

entry.title: Structure of classes of graphs defined by forbidding induced subgraphs
entry.summary: This document is the Habilitation Thesis (Habilitation \`a Diriger des Recherches) of Nicolas Trotignon. It presents his work in structural graph theory, from 2001 to 2009.

entry.title: Carries, group theory, and additive combinatorics
entry.summary: Given a group G and a normal subgroup H we study the problem of choosing coset representatives with few carries.

entry.title: On the uniqueness of solutions for the Fubuki game
entry.summary: We discuss the problem of uniqueness of solutions for the Fubuki game when the diagonal is prescribed.

entry.title: The journey of the union-closed sets conjecture
entry.summary: We survey the state of the union-closed sets conjecture.

entry.title: General removal lemma
entry.summary: We formulate and prove a general result in spirit of hypergraph removal lemma for measurable functions of several variables.

entry.title: A short and elementary proof for a double sum of Brent and Osburn
entry.summary: We present a short and completely elementary proof for a double sum studied by Brent and Osburn in arXiv:1309.2795v2.

entry.title: Operators on Symmetric Polynomials
entry.summary: We provide a brief survey of a certain algebra of operators on symmetric polynomials, and collect a number of previously known results in the field.

entry.title: The Number of Distinct Subsequences of a Random Binary String
entry.summary: We determine the average number of distinct subsequences in a random binary string, and derive an estimate for the average number of distinct subsequences of a particular length.

entry.title: Drawing complete multipartite graphs on the plane with restrictions on crossings
entry.summary: We introduce the concept of NIC-planar graphs and present the full characterization of NIC-planar complete k-partite graphs.

entry.title: Fractional matching in hypergraphs
entry.summary: We find the exact formula for the minimal number of edges of hypergraph which guaranteed fractional matching of cardinality $s$ in the case when $sn$ is integer.

entry.title: On the simultaneous edge coloring of graphs
entry.summary: On the simultaneous edge coloring of graphs

entry.title: Countable connected-homogeneous digraphs
entry.summary: A digraph is connected-homogeneous if every isomorphism between two finite connected induced subdigraphs extends to an automorphism of the whole digraph. In this paper, we completely classify the countable connected-homogeneous digraphs.

entry.title: Triangulations of $Δ_{n-1} \times Δ_{d-1}$ and Matching Ensembles
entry.summary: We suggest an axiom system for a collection of matchings that describes the triangulation of product of simplices.

entry.title: A simplified discharging proof of Grötzsch theorem
entry.summary: In this note, we combine ideas of several previous proofs in order to obtain a quite short proof of Gr\"otzsch theorem.

entry.title: Explicit construction of companion bases
entry.summary: We present a simple procedure for explicitly constructing a companion basis for a quiver mutation equivalent to a simply-laced Dynkin quiver.

entry.title: On transversals of quasialgebraic families of sets
entry.summary: The main results of this paper are generalizations some classical theorems about transversals for families of finite sets to some cases of families of infinite sets.

entry.title: Directed Width Parameters and Circumference of Digraphs
entry.summary: We prove that the directed treewidth, DAG-width and Kelly-width of a digraph are bounded above by its circumference plus one.

entry.title: Lobsters with an almost perfect matching are graceful
entry.summary: Let $T$ be a lobster with a matching that covers all but one vertex. We show that in this case, $T$ is graceful.

entry.title: An easy proof of Gowers' FIN$_k$ theorem
entry.summary: A new proof of Pigeonhole Principle of Gowers is found. The proof does not use of the concept of ultrafilter.

entry.title: Balance in Random Trees
entry.summary: We prove that a random labeled (unlabeled) tree is balanced. We also prove that random labeled and unlabeled trees are strongly $k$-balanced for any $k\geq 3$.

entry.title: Asymptotic series for Hofstadter's figure-figure sequences
entry.summary: We compute asymptotic series for Hofstadter's figure-figure sequences.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Journal of Integer Sequences, Vol. 17 (2014), Article 14.7.2

entry.title: Combinatorial theorems relative to a random set
entry.summary: We describe recent advances in the study of random analogues of combinatorial theorems.
entry.arxiv:comment: 26 pages. Submitted to Proceedings of the ICM 2014

entry.title: A new record for $1324$-avoiding permutations
entry.summary: Refining an existing counting argument, we provide an improved upper bound for the number of 1324-avoiding permutations of a given length.

entry.title: The Cox, Clifford, Möbius, Miquel, and other related configurations and their generalizations
entry.summary: The realizability of countable Cox configurations on Miquelian planes is proved. A simple way to determine the automorphisms of the Cox configurations is presented.

entry.title: Enumeration of Weighted Plane Trees
entry.summary: In weighted trees, all edges are endowed with positive integral weight. We enumerate weighted bicolored plane trees according to their weight and number of edges.

entry.title: The Combinatorial Nullstellensätze Revisited
entry.summary: We revisit and further explore the celebrated Combinatorial Nullstellens\"atze of N. Alon in several different directions.

entry.title: Dimers and Dominoes
entry.summary: Using Kasteleyn's determinant method, we count perfect matchings of rectangular subgraphs of the square grid.
entry.arxiv:comment: Unpublished report, written in 1992, revised in 1997

entry.title: Combinatorial Properties of Mills Ratio
entry.summary: We consider combinatorial properties of the Mills' ratio, and explore the interplay between a continued fraction expansion for the Mills' ratio, the Laplace polynomials and a new family of combinatorial identities.

entry.title: A quantitative version of the Blow-up Lemma
entry.summary: In this paper we give a quantitative version of the Blow-up Lemma.
entry.arxiv:comment: arXiv admin note: substantial text overlap with arXiv:math/9612213

entry.title: There is no circulant weighing matrix of order 60 and weight 36
entry.summary: With the help of a computer, we prove the assertion made in the title.

entry.title: Distinct Distances: Open Problems and Current Bounds
entry.summary: We survey the variants of Erd\H{o}s' distinct distances problem and the current best bounds for each of those.

entry.title: A semigroup identity for tropical 3x3 matrices
entry.summary: We construct a nontrivial identity which holds in the semigroup of tropical 3-by-3 matrices.
entry.arxiv:comment: 8 pages. Minor corrections, some comments added

entry.title: Graphs characterized by the second distance eigenvalue
entry.summary: We characterize all connected graphs with second distance eigenvalue less than $-0.5858$.

entry.title: On the longest k-alternating subsequence
entry.summary: We show that the longest k-alternating substring of a random permutation has length asymptotic to 2 (n-k) / 3.

entry.title: The uncrossing partial order on matchings is Eulerian
entry.summary: We prove that the partial order on the set of matchings of 2n points on a circle, given by resolving crossings, is an Eulerian poset.

entry.title: 2-walks in 2-tough 2k2-free graphs
entry.summary: In this paper, we prove that in every 2-tough 2$K_2$-free graph, there is a 2-walk.

entry.title: Enumeration of Standard Young Tableaux
entry.summary: A survey paper, to appear as a chapter in a forthcoming Handbook on Enumeration.

entry.title: Extremals of the supereigenvector cone in max algebra: a combinatorial description
entry.summary: We give a combinatorial description of extremal generators of the supereigenvector cone {x: Ax>=x} in max algebra.

entry.title: Permutation classes
entry.summary: This is a survey on permutation classes for the upcoming book Handbook of Enumerative Combinatorics.

entry.title: Yet another proof of Brooks' theorem
entry.summary: Arguably the simplest variation of this style of proof as we avoid reducing to the cubic case entirely.
entry.arxiv:comment: A referee for "Brooks' Theorem and Beyond" asked to make this proof available on the arXiv

entry.title: $10$-vertex graphs with cyclic automorphism group of order $4$
entry.summary: We describe computational results about undirected graphs having $10$ vertices and automorphism group isomorphic to $\mathbb{Z}/4\mathbb{Z}$.

entry.title: There are no Coincidences
entry.summary: This paper is inspired by a seqfan post by Jeremy Gardiner. The post listed nine sequences with similar parities. In this paper I prove that the similarities are not a coincidence but a mathematical fact.

entry.title: Refinements of the Rogers-Ramanujan identities
entry.summary: Refinements of the classical Rogers-Ramanujan identities are given in which some parts are weighted. Combinatorial interpretations refining MacMahon's results are corollaries.

entry.title: A 3-to-1 cactus graph: Details
entry.summary: We briefly present a new construction of a 3-to-1 unrecoverable electrical network. This is a taste of a comprehensive forthcoming paper on unrecoverable electrical networks.

entry.title: Counting numerical semigroups
entry.summary: We are interested in formulas for the number of elements in certain classes of numerical semigroups

entry.title: Gallai's Theorem
entry.summary: This paper presents a proof of Gallai's Theorem, adapted from A. Soifer's presentation in The Mathematical Coloring Book of E. Witt's 1952 proof of Gallai's Theorem.

entry.title: Modifications of Tutte-Grothendieck invariants and Tutte polynomials
entry.summary: We transform Tutte-Grothedieck invariants thus also Tutte polynomials on matroids so that the contraction-deletion rule for loops (isthmuses) coincides with the general case.

entry.title: Sublinear extensions of polygons
entry.summary: Every convex $n$-gon is a projection of a polytope with $o(n)$ facets.

entry.title: Topological cycle matroids of infinite graphs
entry.summary: We prove that the topological cycles of an arbitrary infinite graph induce a matroid. This matroid in general is neither finitary nor cofinitary.
entry.arxiv:comment: arXiv admin note: substantial text overlap with arXiv:1409.6640

entry.title: A bijection between certain quarter plane walks and Motzkin paths
entry.summary: This short note gives a bijection between quarter plane walks using the steps $\{\rightarrow, \searrow, \downarrow, \leftarrow, \nwarrow, \uparrow\}$ and bicoloured Motzkin paths.

entry.title: On uniform recurrence of morphic sequences
entry.summary: We describe a shorter algorithm for HD0L uniform recurrence problem

entry.title: Integrality of the simple Hurwitz numbers
entry.summary: We show the integrality of the simple Hurwitz numbers. The main tool is the cut-and-join operator, and our proof is a purely combinatorial one.

entry.title: Plane partitions and their pedestal polynomials
entry.summary: We define, for an arbitrary partially ordered set, a multi-variable polynomial generalizing the hook polynomial.

entry.title: Forests of chord diagrams with a given number of trees
entry.summary: In this short note, we find the number of forests of chord diagrams with a given number of trees and a given number of chords.

entry.title: Ribbon graph minors and low-genus partial duals
entry.summary: We give an excluded minor characterisation of the class of ribbon graphs that admit partial duals of Euler genus at most one.

entry.title: A Method to construct the Sparse-paving Matroids over a Finite Set
entry.summary: We give a method to construct the sparse-paving matroids over a finit det S.

entry.title: Factorizations related to the reciprocal Pascal matrix
entry.summary: The reciprocal Pascal matrix has entries $\binom{i+j}{j}^{-1}$. Explicit formullae for its LU-decomposition, the LU-decomposition of its inverse, and some related matrices are obtained. For all results, $q$-analogues are also presented.

entry.title: Castelnuovo-Mumford regularity of graphs
entry.summary: We present new combinatorial insights into the calculation of (Castelnuovo-Mumford) regularity of graphs.

entry.title: Residues and the Combinatorial Nullstellensatz
entry.summary: We interpret the Combinatorial Nullstellensatz of Noga Alon as a multidimensional residue formula, describe some consequences of this interpretation and related open problems.

entry.title: A Ratio of Alternants Formula for Loop Schur Functions
entry.summary: We prove a ratio of alternants formula for loop Schur functions, and we give a new proof of the loop Murnaghan-Nakayama rule.

entry.title: Odd number and Trapezoidal number
entry.summary: In this paper, we give a bijective proof of the reduced lecture hall partition theorem. It is possible to extend this bijection in lecture hall partition theorem. And refined versions of each theorems are also presented.

entry.title: Dimensional dual hyperovals in classical polar spaces
entry.summary: In this paper we show that n-dimensional dual hyperovals cannot exist in all but one classical polar space of rank n if n is even. This resolves a question posed by Yoshiara.

entry.title: Classification of reflexibile regular Cayley maps for dihedral groups
entry.summary: In this paper, we classify reflexible regular Cayley maps for dihedral groups.

entry.title: On exponential growth of degrees
entry.summary: A short proof to a recent theorem of Giambruno and Mishchenko is given in this note.

entry.title: Projective Space: Lines and Duality
entry.summary: We offer an axiomatic presentation of three-dimensional projective space that adopts the line as its fundamental element and renders automatic the principle of duality.

entry.title: Permutation patterns: basic definitions and notation
entry.summary: A brief presentation of basic definitions and notation used in permutation patterns research.

entry.title: On the number of edges in the special distance graph
entry.summary: In this paper we obtain new estimates of the number of edges in subgraphs of the special distance graph. Bibliography: 21 item.

entry.title: Courte preuve d'une identité comportant les nombres de Bernoulli
entry.summary: In this paper, we give a short proof of a relation generalizing many identities for Bernoulli numbers.

entry.title: Projective Space: Reguli and Projectivity
entry.summary: We investigate an `assumption of projectivity' that is appropriate to the self-dual axiomatic formulation of three-dimensional projective space.

entry.title: Two Extensions of the Sury's Identity
entry.summary: In this note we prove two extensions of the Sury's identity.

entry.title: Mitosis algorithm for Grothendieck polynomials
entry.summary: In this article we will introduce the way to extend the mitosis algorithm for Schubert polynomials, developed by Ezra Miller, to the case of Grothendieck polynomials.

entry.title: A Lucas-type congruence for q-Delannoy numbers
entry.summary: We prove a Lucas-type congruence for q-Delannoy numbers.
entry.arxiv:comment: 11 pages. This is a preliminary draft

entry.title: What is the minimal cardinal of a family which shatters all d-subsets of a finite set?
entry.summary: What is the minimal cardinal of a family which shatters all d-subsets of a finite set?

entry.title: Syzygies on Tutte polynomials of freedom matroids
entry.summary: We give a generating set for linear relations on Tutte polynomials of rank-$r$ size-$n$ freedom matroids.

entry.title: A note on enumerating colored integer partitions
entry.summary: In this short note, we give basic enumerative results on colored integer partitions.

entry.title: Index theory for partial-bijections
entry.summary: We offer streamlined proofs of fundamental theorems regarding the index theory for partial self-maps of an infinite set that are bijective between cofinite subsets.

entry.title: Fractional boxicity of graphs
entry.summary: In this note, we define the fractional boxicity of a graph that is a lower bound for the boxicity of the graph.

entry.title: Cluster Algebras and Symmetries of Regular Tilings
entry.summary: The classification of Grassmannian cluster algebras resembles that of regular polygonal tilings. We conjecture that this resemblance may indicate a deeper connection between these seemingly unrelated structures.

entry.title: $h$-perfect plane triangulations
entry.summary: We characterise $t$-perfect plane triangulations by forbidden induced subgraphs. As a consequence, we obtain that a plane triangulation is $h$-perfect if and only if it is perfect.

entry.title: Combinatorially rigid simple polytopes with d+3 facets
entry.summary: We classify here combinatorially rigid simple polytopes with three facets more than their dimension.

entry.title: A Universal Closed Form For Square Matrix Powers
entry.summary: This note presents a simple, universal closed form for the powers of any square matrix. A diligent search of the internet gave no indication that the form is known.

entry.title: On the number of Steiner triple systems S(2^m-1,3,2) of rank 2^m - m + 2 over GF(2)
entry.summary: We obtain the number of different Steiner triple systems S(2^m-1,3,2) of rank 2^m-m+2 over the field GF(2).

entry.title: Cyclic elliptic spreads
entry.summary: Moderately large numbers of transitive elliptic spreads are constructed in characteristic $2$ and dimension $\equiv $ 2 (mod 4).

entry.title: Restricted Product Sets under Unique Representability
entry.summary: We prove some results of Kemperman--Scherk type for restricted product sets in multiplicative groups of fields (in particular, for cyclic groups). The proofs use polynomial method.

entry.title: Minimal supports of eigenfunctions of Hamming graphs
entry.summary: We find minimal supports of eigenfunctions of Hamming graphs for eigenvalue n(q-1)-q and describe eigenfunctions with minimal support.

entry.title: Exposition of Elekes Szabo paper
entry.summary: We explain the Elekes Szabo paper in more details and improve the constant in one dimensional case in \mathbb{R} and \mathbb{C}.
entry.arxiv:comment: This is the Master thesis of the author

entry.title: Scattered Spaces in Galois Geometry
entry.summary: This is a survey paper on the theory of scattered spaces in Galois geometry and its applications.

entry.title: Equivariant Euler characteristics of partition posets
entry.summary: We compute all the equivariant Euler characteristics of the $\Sigma_n$-poset of partitions of the $n$ element set.

entry.title: The antichain of excluded minors for the class of gammoids is maximal
entry.summary: Every gammoid is a minor of an excluded minor for the class of gammoids.

entry.title: Enumeration of 4-regular one-face maps
entry.summary: We give explicit formulas enumerating 4-regular labelled and unlabelled one-face maps.

entry.title: Discrete quantitative nodal theorem
entry.summary: In this note we prove a result that can be thought of as a common generalization of the Nodal Theorem and (one direction of) Cheeger's Inequality for graphs.

entry.title: A short conceptual proof of Narayana's path-counting formula
entry.summary: We deduce Narayana's formula for the number of lattice paths that fit in a Young diagram as a direct consequence of the Gessel-Viennot theorem on non-intersecting lattice paths.
