entry.title: Configurations of conjugate permutations
entry.summary: We describe some configurations of conjugate permutations which may be used as a mathematical model of some genetical processes and crystal growth.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Quasigroups and Related Systems vol. 18 (2010), pp. 17-24

entry.title: Orthogonality graph of the algebra of upper triangular matrices
entry.summary: We study the connectedness and the diameter of orthogonality graphs of upper triangular matrix algebras over arbitrary fields.

entry.title: Logarithmic form of Lagrange inversion formula
entry.summary: We give presentation of composition inverse of formal power serie in a logarithmic form.

entry.title: Note: a counterexample to a conjecture of Jackson about hamiltonicity of diregular digraphs
entry.summary: $3$-diregular circulant digraph on $12$ vertices is a counterexample of Jackson's conjecture about hamiltonicity of diregular digraphs

entry.title: A bijection for two sequences in OEIS
entry.summary: We show that sequences A026737 and A111279 in The On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences are the same by giving a bijection between two classes of Grand Schroder paths.

entry.title: Octahedral, dicyclic and special linear solutions of some unsolved Hamilton-Waterloo problems
entry.summary: We give a sharply-vertex-transitive solution of each of the nine Hamilton-Waterloo problems left open by Danziger, Quattrocchi and Stevens.

entry.title: Solution of Hypergraph Turan problem
entry.summary: Using original {\it Symmetrical Smoothing Method} we solve $(3,k)$- hypergraph Turan problem

entry.title: Order nine MMIK graphs
entry.summary: We show that there are exactly eight MMIK (minor minimal intrinsically knotted) graphs of order nine.
entry.arxiv:comment: 11 pages, 3 figures, submitted to Contemporary Mathematics

entry.title: Hamiltonian prisms on 5-chordal graphs
entry.summary: In this paper, we provide a method to find a Hamiltonian cycle in the prism of a 5-chordal graph, which is $(1+\epsilon)$-tough, with some special conditions.

entry.title: Symmetries related to domino tilings on a chessboard
entry.summary: In this paper we study different kinds of symmetries related to the domino tilings of chessboards.

entry.title: On the diameter of Kronecker graphs
entry.summary: It is shown that a.a.s. as soon as a Kronecker graph becomes connected its diameter is bounded by a constant.

entry.title: On a conjecture of Cigler
entry.summary: A conjecture of Cigler which realizes normalized q-Hermite polynomials as moments is verified.

entry.title: Inverting the Sweep Map on (2n,n)-Dyck Paths: A Simple Algorithm
entry.summary: We introduce a simple, rank-based algorithm for inverting the sweep map on (2n,n)-Dyck paths.

entry.title: Almost all matroids are non-representable
entry.summary: We prove that, as $n$ approaches infinity, the proportion of $n$-element matroids that are representable tends to zero.
entry.arxiv:comment: Newer version contains some minor tweaks and corrections

entry.title: Ehrhart polynomials of 3-dimensional simple integral convex polytopes
entry.summary: We give an explicit formula on the Ehrhart polynomial of a 3-dimensional simple integral convex polytope by using toric geometry.

entry.title: Counting Spanning trees in double nested graphs
entry.summary: In this paper we give a linear time algorithm for computing the number of spanninig trees in double nested graphs.

entry.title: A Conjecture about Periods in Subtraction Games
entry.summary: We make a conjecture that characterizes the periods of the nim values in subtraction games with subtraction set of size 3.

entry.title: From Chio Pivotal Condensation to the Matrix-Tree theorem
entry.summary: We show a determinant identity which generalizes both the Chio pivotal condensation theorem and the Matrix-Tree theorem.

entry.title: Summation formulas involving generalized harmonic numbers
entry.summary: In terms of the derivative operator and three hypergeometric series identities, several interesting summation formulas involving generalized harmonic numbers are established.

entry.title: Saalschütz's theorem and summation formulae involving generalized harmonic numbers
entry.summary: In terms of the derivative operator, integral operator and Saalsch\"{u}tz's theorem, two families of summation formulae involving generalized harmonic numbers are established.

entry.title: Designs for 24-vertex snarks
entry.summary: The design spectrum problem is solved for the thirty-eight 24-vertex non-trivial snarks.
entry.arxiv:comment: 74 pages. Abridged version (omitting the Appendix) accepted by Utilitas Mathematica

entry.title: Upper Bounds for the Number of Solutions to Spatially Coupled Sudokus
entry.summary: Based on combinatorics, we evaluate the upper bounds for the number of solutions to spatially coupled Sudokus, which are popular logic puzzles.

entry.title: $m$-Modular Wythoff
entry.summary: We discuss a variant of Wythoff's Game, $m$-Modular Wythoff's Game, and identify the winning and losing positions for this game.

entry.title: Convex domino towers
entry.summary: We study convex domino towers using a classic dissection technique on polyominoes to find the generating function and an asymptotic approximation.

entry.title: On chromatic numbers of some distance graphs
entry.summary: In this paper we find chromatic numbers of distance graphs $G(n,3,2)$ for infinitely many n. Also we improve upper bound for $\chi(G(n,r,s))$ in large part of cases.

entry.title: A badly expanding set on the $2$-torus
entry.summary: We give a counterexample to a conjecture stated in Linial and London 2006 regarding expansion on $\mathbb{T}^2$ under $\begin{bmatrix}1&1\\ 0&1\end{bmatrix}$ and $\begin{bmatrix}1&0\\ 1&1\end{bmatrix}$.

entry.title: Hyperpfaffians
entry.summary: We define and inverstigate a generalization of the pfaffian for multiple array which interpolate between the hyperdeterminant and the hyperp-faffian.

entry.title: The Pegasus Tiles: an aperiodic pair of tiles
entry.summary: The Pegasus tiles are an aperiodic pair of tiles with "tip to tip" matching rules, first drawn in 1996. We present them here.

entry.title: The Trilobite and Crab: a full explanation
entry.summary: The trilobite and crab are among the very simplest aperiodic sets of tiles known: two tiles in eight translation classes. Yet the proof that they are an aperiodic set is surprisingly complex.

entry.title: Matching Rules for the Sphinx Tiling Substitution
entry.summary: We give a set of tiles that enforces the sphinx tiling substitution system; the tiles are thus aperiodic.

entry.title: Two-connected spanning subgraphs with at most $\frac{10}{7}$OPT edges
entry.summary: We present a $\frac{10}{7}$-approximation algorithm for the minimum two-vertex-connected spanning subgraph problem.

entry.title: Representing derivatives of Chebyshev polynomials by Chebyshev polynomials
entry.summary: A recursion formula for derivatives of Chebyshev polynomials is replaced by an explicit formula.

entry.title: Lp Expander Graphs
entry.summary: We discuss how the graph expander property is related to the behavior of Lp functions on the covering tree.

entry.title: Abelian Ramsey Length and Asymptotic Lower Bounds
entry.summary: This technical note aims at evaluating an asymptotic lower bound on abelian Ramsey lengths.

entry.title: A brief introduction to Spectral Graph Theory
entry.summary: Expanded lecture notes. Preliminary version, comments are welcome.

entry.title: How many delta-matroids are there?
entry.summary: We give upper and lower bounds on the number of delta-matroids, and on the number of even delta-matroids.

entry.title: Classification of $Q$-multiplicity-free skew Schur $Q$-functions
entry.summary: We classify the $Q$-multiplicity-free skew Schur $Q$-functions. Towards this result, we also provide new relations between the shifted Littlewood-Richardson coefficients.

entry.title: Three Ways to Count Walks in a Digraph
entry.summary: We approach the problem of counting the number of walks in a digraph from three different perspectives: enumerative combinatorics, linear algebra, and symbolic dynamics.

entry.title: Some elementary observations on Narayana polynomials and related topics
entry.summary: We give an elementary account of generalized Fibonacci and Lucas polynomials whose moments are Narayana polynomials of type A and type B.

entry.title: An algebraic proof of determinant formulas of Grothendieck polynomials
entry.summary: We give an algebraic proof of the determinant formulas for factorial Grothendieck polynomials obtained by Hudson--Ikeda--Matsumura--Naruse and by Hudson--Matsumura.

entry.title: Projective Space: Points and Planes
entry.summary: We take points and planes as fundamental, lines as derived, in an axiomatic formulation of three-dimensional projective space, the self-dual nature of which formulation renders automatic the principle of duality.

entry.title: Diameter and Automorphisms of Gelfand-Tsetlin Polytopes
entry.summary: We determine the diameter of the 1-skeleton and the combinatorial automorphism group of any Gelfand-Tsetlin polytope GT$_{\lambda}$ associated to an integer partition $\lambda.$

entry.title: Bounds on Network Codes for the Homogeneous Weight
entry.summary: We give upper bounds on the size of a code whose fundamental parameters are determined by a a directed acyclic graph. These are extensions of Plotkin and Elias bounds of classical coding theory.

entry.title: Discretized Sum-Product Estimates in Matrix Algebras
entry.summary: We generalize Bourgain's discretized sum-product theorem to matrix algebras.

entry.title: Eulerian polynomials and polynomial congruences
entry.summary: We prove that the Eulerian polynomial satisfies certain polynomial congruences. Furthermore, these congruences characterize the Eulerian polynomial.

entry.title: Projective Space: Tetrads and Harmonicity
entry.summary: Within an axiomatic framework for three-dimensional projective space based on lines alone, we explore the Fano axiom of harmonicity according to which the diagonal lines of a complete quadrilateral are not concurrent.

entry.title: Saito duality and the classical theory of arithmetic functions
entry.summary: We study Saito duality and Fourier-Ramanujan transform for power sums and multiplicities of monodromy roots.

entry.title: The integrally representable trees of norm 3
entry.summary: In this paper, we determine the integrally representable trees of norm 3.

entry.title: Projective Space: Harmonicity and Projectivity
entry.summary: For an axiomatization of three-dimensional projective space based on points and planes, we discuss appropriate versions of the harmonicity axiom and the projectivity axiom, showing that each axiom is equivalent to its spatial dual.

entry.title: Subcritical graph classes containing all planar graphs
entry.summary: We construct minor-closed addable families of graphs that are subcritical and contain all planar graphs. This contradicts (one direction of) a well-known conjecture of Noy.

entry.title: Equivariant Euler characteristics of subspace posets
entry.summary: We compute the (primary) equivariant Euler characteristics of the building for the general linear group over a finite field.

entry.title: Some divisibility properties of binomial coefficients
entry.summary: In this paper, we gave some properties of binomial coefficient.

entry.title: A Note on Weak Dirac Conjecture
entry.summary: We show that every set $\mathcal{P}$ of $n$ non-collinear points in the plane contains a point incident to at least $\lceil\frac{n}{3}\rceil+1$ of the lines determined by $\mathcal{P}$.

entry.title: A characterization of 2-dimensional Cayley graphs on dihedral groups
entry.summary: In this paper we characterize all of Cayley graphs on dihedral groups with metric dimension two.

entry.title: Speyer's elegant topological proof for Kasteleyn's Theorem
entry.summary: The purpose of this note is to rephrase Speyer's elegant topological proof for Kasteleyn's Theorem in a simple graph theoretical manner.

entry.title: Infinitly many excluded minors for frame matroids and for lifted-graphic matroids
entry.summary: We present infinite sequences of excluded minors for both the class of lifted-graphic matroids and the class of frame matroids.

entry.title: Local Finiteness of Infinite Neighbor Complexes
entry.summary: We show that if the neighbor complex, as defined by H.~Scarf, of an infinite subset of $\Z^n$ has finite dimension, then each vertex has finitely many neighbors.

entry.title: Inverting the Sweep Map on (kn,n)-Dyck Paths: A Simple Algorithm
entry.summary: We show that our algorithm for inverting the sweep map on (2n, n)-Dyck paths works for any (kn, n)-Dyck path, where k is an arbitrary positive integer.

entry.title: Sticky matroids and Kantor's Conjecture
entry.summary: We prove the equivalence of Kantor's Conjecture and the Sticky Matroid Conjecture due to Poljak und Turz\'ik.

entry.title: Factorization formulas of $K$-$k$-Schur functions II
entry.summary: Subsequently to the author's preceding paper, we give full proofs of some explicit formulas about factorizations of $K$-$k$-Schur functions associated with any multiple $k$-rectangles.

entry.title: Self-dual Harmonicity: the planar case
entry.summary: We present a manifestly geometrically self-dual version of the Fano harmonicity axiom for the projective plane.

entry.title: Independent and maximal branching packing in infinite matroid-rooted digraphs
entry.summary: We prove a common generalization of the maximal independent arborescence packing theorem of Cs. Kir\'aly and two of our earlier works about packing branchings in infinite digraphs.

entry.title: A Cheeger-Buser-Type inequality on CW complexes
entry.summary: We extend the definition of boundary expansion to CW complexes and prove a Cheeger-Buser-Type relation between the spectral gap of the Laplacian and the expansion of an orientable CW complex.

entry.title: Schubert polynomials, 132-patterns, and Stanley's conjecture
entry.summary: Motivated by a recent conjecture of R. P. Stanley we offer a lower bound for the sum of the coefficients of a Schubert polynomial in terms of $132$-pattern containment.

entry.title: Gaps in full homomorphism order
entry.summary: We characterise gaps in the full homomorphism order of graphs.

entry.title: Families of vectors without antipodal pairs
entry.summary: Some Erd\H{o}s-Ko-Rado type extremal properties of families of vectors from $\{-1,0,1\}^n$ are considered.

entry.title: A lower bound for the size of Kakeya sets with respect to hyperplanes in $\mathbb{F}_q^n$
entry.summary: We prove that a subset of $\mathbb{F}_q^n$ that contains a hyperplane in any direction has size at least $q^{n}-O(q^2)$.

entry.title: Distance-regular graphs without 4-claws
entry.summary: We determine the distance-regular graphs with diameter at least $3$ and $c_2\geq 2$ but without induced $K_{1,4}$-subgraphs.

entry.title: Metric dimension of Andrasfai graphs
entry.summary: In this paper we determine the metric dimension of Andrasfai graphs and some related graphs.

entry.title: A curious identity and its applications to partitions with bounded part differences
entry.summary: In this note, we present a curious $q$-series identity with applications to certain partitions with bounded part differences.

entry.title: Equivariant Euler characteristics of the unitary building
entry.summary: We determine all the equivariant Euler characteristics of the building for the general unitary group over a finite field.

entry.title: New Cameron-Liebler line classes with parameter $\frac{q^2+1}{2}$
entry.summary: New families of Cameron-Liebler line classes of ${\rm PG}(3,q)$, $q\ge 7$ odd, with parameter $(q^2+1)/2$ are constructed.

entry.title: The set of alternating sign matrices which are determined by their X-ray is a member of the Catalan family
entry.summary: We exhibit a bijection between Dyck paths and alternating sign matrices which are determined by their antidiagonal sums.

entry.title: New 5-designs---revisited
Free arrangements with low exponents
entry.summary: In this note we show that any free hyperplane arrangement with exponents 1's and 2's is a supersolvable arrangement.

entry.title: The square of a planar cubic graph is $7$-colorable
entry.summary: We prove the conjecture made by G.Wegner in 1977 that the square of every planar, cubic graph is $7$-colorable. Here, $7$ cannot be replaced by $6$.

entry.title: On Some Properties of Tribonacci Quaternions
entry.summary: In this paper, we give some properties of the Tribonacci and Tribonacci-Lucas quaternions and obtain some identities for them.

entry.title: Elementary proof of congruences involving sum of binomial coefficients
entry.summary: We provide elementary proof of several congruences involving single sum and multisums of binomial coefficients.

entry.title: Construction of Identities for Sums of Squares
entry.summary: From sum-of-squares formulas of sizes $[r, s, n]$ and $[r', s', n']$ we construct a formula of size $[r + r', 2ss', 2nn']$.

entry.title: Beta-Function Identities via Probabilistic Approach
entry.summary: Using a probabilistic approach, we derive several interesting identities involving beta functions. Our results generalize certain well-known combinatorial identities involving binomial coefficients and gamma functions.

entry.title: Another Combinatorial Determinant
entry.summary: We present a variation and generalization of a determinant evaluation of Wilf (math.CO/9809120). His result concerns a matrix whose entries are the coefficients of powers of a given power series; we replace the powers by repeated compositions and obtain similar results.
entry.arxiv:comment: 3 pages, AMSLaTeX source (replaced 18 May 1998: corrected some typos, added a reference provided by Herb Wilf)

entry.title: q and q,t-Analogs of Non-commutative Symmetric Functions
entry.summary: We introduce two families of non-commutative symmetric functions that have analogous properties to the Hall-Littlewood and Macdonald symmetric functions.
entry.arxiv:comment: Different from analogues in math.CO/0106191 - v2: 26 pages - added a definition in terms of triangularity/scalar product relations - to be submitted FPSAC'02

entry.title: Evaluations of some determinants of matrices related to the Pascal triangle
entry.summary: We prove several evaluations of determinants of matrices, the entries of which are given by the recurrence $a_{i,j}=a_{i-1,j}+a_{i,j-1}$, or variations thereof. These evaluations were either conjectured or extend conjectures by Roland Bacher [J. Th\'eorie Nombres Bordeaux 13 (2001), to appear; see http://arxiv.org/abs/math.CO/0109013].
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: S\'eminaire Lotharingien Combin. 47 (2002), Article B47g, 19 pp.

entry.title: The Floyd-Warshall Algorithm, the AP and the TSP, Part II
entry.summary: In math.CO/0111309, we used admissible permutations and a variant of the Floyd-Warshall Algorithm to obtain an optimal solution to the Assignment Problem and an approximate solution to the Traveling Salesman Problem. Here we give a large, detailed illustration of how the algorithms are applied.
entry.arxiv:comment: Text in Word 2000, math in Math Type 4.0, sent in a PDF file written in Acrobat 5.0, 63 pages

entry.title: Differential Operators and Weighted Isobaric Polynomials
entry.summary: We characterize those sequences of weighted isobaric polynomials as defined in math.CO/0106213 which belong to the kernel of the linear operator $D_{11} - \sum_{j=1}^k a_j t_j D_{2j} - mD_2$, and we characterize those linear operators of this form in terms of the coefficients $a_j$ which have a non-zero kernel.

entry.title: Lagrangian Matroids: Representations of Type $B_n$
entry.summary: We introduce the concept of orientation for Lagrangian matroids represented in the flag variety of maximal isotropic subspaces of dimension N in the real vector space of dimension 2N+1. The paper continues the study started in math.CO/0209100.

entry.title: Recent developments in algebraic combinatorics
entry.summary: A survey of three recent developments in algebraic combinatorics: (1) the Laurent phenomenon, (2) Gromov-Witten invariants and toric Schur functions, and (3) toric h-vectors and intersection cohomology. This paper is a continuation of "Recent progress in algebraic combinatorics" (math.CO/0010218), which dealt with three other topics.

entry.title: On generating series of complementary planar trees
entry.summary: We generalize and reprove an identity of Parker and Loday. It states that certain pairs of generating series associated to pairs of labelled rooted planar trees are mutually inverse under composition.
entry.arxiv:comment: 27 pages, 2 figures, contains a discussion of Loday's example (i) (math.CO/0403316, v1). Preprint 649 of the Institut Fourier

entry.title: Ehrhart polynomials of cyclic polytopes
entry.summary: The Ehrhart polynomial of an integral convex polytope counts the number of lattice points in dilates of the polytope. In math.CO/0402148, the authors conjectured that for any cyclic polytope with integral parameters, the Ehrhart polynomial of it is equal to its volume plus the Ehrhart polynomial of its lower envelope and proved the case when the dimension d = 2. In our article, we prove the conjecture for any dimension.

entry.title: Heterochromatic tree partition number of a complete multipartite graph
entry.summary: This paper has been withdrawn by the author(s), due an error in the proof.

entry.title: Periodic Schur process and cylindric partitions
entry.summary: Periodic Schur process is a generalization of the Schur process introduced in math.CO/0107056. We compute its correlation functions and their bulk scaling limits, and discuss several applications including asymptotic analysis of uniform measures on cylindric partitions, time-dependent extensions of the discrete sine kernel, and bulk limit behavior of certain measures on partitions introduced in hep-th/0306238 in connection with supersymmetric gauge theories.

entry.title: A conjectured combinatorial interpretation of the normalized irreducible character values of the symmetric group
entry.summary: In math.CO/0109093 the author obtained a formula for the value of an irreducible symmetric group character indexed by a partition of rectangular shape. In the present paper this formula is (conjecturally) generalized to arbitrary shapes.

entry.title: The number of permutations with a given number of sequences
entry.summary: P(n,s) denotes the number of permutations of 1,2,...n that have exactly s sequences. Canfield and Wilf [math.CO/0609704] recently showed that P(n,s) can be written as a sum of s polynomials in n. We determine these polynomials explicitly and also obtain explicit expressions for P(n,s) and its fixed-s generating function u_s(x).

entry.title: On some properties of permutation tableaux
entry.summary: We consider the relation between various permutation statistics and properties of permutation tableaux. We answer some of the questions of Steingrimsson and Williams (math.CO/0507149), in particular, on the distribution of the bistatistic of numbers of rows and essential ones in permutation tableaux. We also consider and enumerate sets of permutation tableaux related to some pattern restrictions on permutations.

entry.title: A Note on the Critical Group of a Line Graph
entry.summary: This note answers a question posed by Levine in arkiv:math.CO/0906.2809. The main result is Theorem 1 which shows that under certain circumstances a critical group of a directed graph is the quotient of a critical group of its directed line graph.
entry.arxiv:comment: 6 pages. Added details to the proof of Theorem 1. Fixed typos

entry.title: Two Vignettes On Full Rook Placements
entry.summary: Using bijections between pattern-avoiding permutations and certain full rook placements on Ferrers boards, we give short proofs of two enumerative results. The first is a simplified enumeration of the 3124, 1234-avoiding permutations, obtained recently by Callan via a complicated decomposition. The second is a streamlined bijection between 1342-avoiding permutations and permutations which can be sorted by two increasing stacks in series, originally due to Atkinson, Murphy, and Ru\v{s}kuc.

entry.title: On Two OEIS Conjectures
entry.summary: Stephan (Prove or Disprove 100 Conjectures from the OES, arXiv:math/0409509v4 [math.CO])enumerates a number of conjectures regarding integer sequences contained in Sloane's On-line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences (N. J. A. Sloane, editor, The On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, published electronically at https://oeis.org). In this paper, we prove two of these conjectures.

entry.title: Longest increasing subsequences of random colored permutations
entry.summary: We compute the limit distribution for (centered and scaled) length of the longest increasing subsequence of random colored permutations. The limit distribution function is a power of that for usual random permutations computed recently by Baik, Deift, and Johansson (math.CO/9810105). In two--colored case our method provides a different proof of a similar result by Tracy and Widom about longest increasing subsequences of signed permutations (math.CO/9811154). Our main idea is to reduce the `colored' problem to the case of usual random permutations using certain combinatorial results and elementary probabilistic arguments.

entry.title: Rational function certification of multisum/integral/``$q$'' identities
entry.summary: The method of rational function certification for proving terminating hypergeometric identities is extended from single sums or integrals to multi-integral/sums and ``$q$'' integral/sums.

entry.title: A WZ proof of Ramanujan's Formula for Pi
entry.summary: Ramanujan's series for Pi, that appeared in his famous letter to Hardy, is given a one-line WZ proof.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: ``Geometry, Analysis, and Mechanics'', (J. M. Rassias, ed.), World Scientific, Singapore, 1994, 107-108

entry.title: Chu's 1303 Identity Implies Bombieri's 1990 Norm-Inequality [via an Identity of Beauzamy and Dégot]
entry.summary: The Vandermonde-Chu Binomial Coefficients Identity is shown to imply Bombieri's deep norm inequalities, via identities of Beauzamy-D\'egot, and Reznick.

entry.title: Three Recitations on Holonomic Systems and Hypergeometric Series
entry.summary: A tutorial on what later became to be known as WZ theory, as well as a motivated account of the seminal Gosper algorithm.

entry.title: A High-School Algebra and high-school (purely formal) calculus,. Wallet-Sized Proof, of the Bieberbach Conjecture [after L. Weinstein]
entry.summary: L. Weinstein's brilliant short proof of de Branges's Theorem is made even shorter by using computer algebra.

entry.title: Tiling a rectangle with the fewest squares
entry.summary: We show that a square-tiling of a $p\times q$ rectangle, where $p$ and $q$ are relatively prime integers, has at least $\log_2p$ squares. If $q>p$ we construct a square-tiling with less than $q/p+C\log p$ squares of integer size, for some universal constant $C$.

entry.title: Aztec diamonds, checkerboard graphs, and spanning trees
entry.summary: This note derives the characteristic polynomial of a graph that represents nonjump moves in a generalized game of checkers. The number of spanning trees is also determined.

entry.title: DX-operator expansion
entry.summary: We characterize those linear operators that can be expressed as a sum over k of terms of the form f_k(D) x^k and give several examples.

entry.title: Proof of a conjecture of Narayana on dominance refinements of the Smirnov two-sample test
entry.summary: We prove the following conjecture of Narayana: there are no dominance refinements of the Smirnov two-sample test if and only if the two sample sizes are relatively prime.

entry.title: Maple umbral calculus package
entry.summary: We are developing a Maple package of functions related to Rota's Umbral Calculus. A Mathematica version of this package is being developed in parallel.

entry.title: A finite partition theorem with double exponential bounds
entry.summary: We prove that double exponentiation is an upper bound to Ramsey theorem for colouring of pairs when we want to predetermine the order of the differences of successive members of the homogeneous set.

entry.title: VLSI layouts and DNA physical mappings
entry.summary: We show that an important problem ($k$-ICG) in computational biology is equivalent to a colored version of a well-known graph layout problem ($k$-CVS).

entry.title: Overlapping Pfaffians
entry.summary: A combinatorial construction proves an identity for the product of the Pfaffian of a skew-symmetric matrix by the Pfaffian of one of its submatrices. Several applications of this identity are followed by a brief history of Pfaffians.

entry.title: Self Avoiding Walks, the Language of Science, and Fibonacci Numbers
entry.summary: The Bordelaise philosophy, or rather a juvenile version of it, is used to enumerate self avoiding walks in a $[0,1] \times (- \infty, \infty)$.

entry.title: The Method of Undetermined Generalization and Specialization Illustrated with Fred Galvin's Amazing Proof of the Dinitz Conjecture
entry.summary: Fred Galvin's amazing proof of the Dinitiz conjecture is used to illustrate the method of undetermined generalization and specialization.

entry.title: Reverend Charles to the aid of Major Percy and Fields-Medalist Enrico
entry.summary: Dodgson's determinant condensation rule is shown to immediately imply the evaluation of MacMahon's determinant expression that leads to the Box Theorem.

entry.title: Sierksma's Dutch Cheese Problem
entry.summary: Consider partitions, of a cardinality $(q-1)(d+1)+1$ generic subset of euclidean $d$-space, into $q$ parts whose convex hulls have a nonempty intersection. We show that if these partitions are counted with appropriate signs $\pm 1$ then the answer is always $((q-1)!)^d$. Also some other related results are given.

entry.title: Order complexes of noncomplemented lattices are nonevasive
entry.summary: We reprove and generalize in a combinatorial way the result of A. Bj\"orner [J.\ Comb.\ Th.\ A {\bf 30}, 1981, pp.~90--100, Theorem 3.3], that order complexes of noncomplemented lattices are contractible, namely by showing that these simplicial complexes are in fact nonevasive, in particular collapsible.

entry.title: How often is a permutation an n'th power?
entry.summary: We give a short argument that for any fixed n, the probability that a permutation on m letters is an n'th power is asymptotically C m^{phi(n)/n - 1}.

entry.title: Descent identities, Hessenberg varieties, and the Weil conjectures
entry.summary: The Weil Conjectures are applied to the Hessenberg Varieties to obtain interesting information about the combinatorics of descents in the symmetric group. Combining this with elementary linear algebra leads to elegant proofs of some identities from the theory of descents.

entry.title: An overview of domino and lozenge tilings
entry.summary: We consider tilings of quadriculated regions by dominoes and of triangulated regions by lozenges. We present an overview of results concerning tileability, enumeration and the structure of the space of tilings.

entry.title: Faster and Faster convergent series for $ζ(3)$
entry.summary: Using WZ pairs we present an infinite family of accelerated series for computing $\zeta(3)$.

entry.title: Curing the Andrews syndrom
entry.summary: George Andrews's recent challenge to automated identity-proving and the WZ method is dealt with. It is argued that the rivalry between the classical and automated approaches to hypergeometric sums is beneficial to both.
entry.arxiv:comment: Plain TeX, to appear in J. Difference Eq. Appl

entry.title: A note on generalized chromatic number and generalized girth
entry.summary: Erd\H{o}s proved that there are graphs with arbitrarily large girth and chromatic number. We study the extension of this for generalized chromatic numbers.

entry.title: A Heterosexual Mehler Formula for the Straight Hermite Polynomials (A La Foata)
entry.summary: The celebrated Foata combinatorial model for Hermite polynomials, and his seminal and beautiful proof of the Mehler formula, are straightened to deal with two sexes rather than one, with the exclusion of same-sex relationships (both marital and non-marital).

entry.title: Proof of Conway's Lost Cosmological Theorem
entry.summary: John Horton Conway's Cosmological Theorem, about Audioactive sequences, for which no extant proof existed, is given a computer-generated proof, hopefully for good.
